es-and-arenas-are-now-going-to-have-to-answer-for-this-3576307">显示，草根场馆正面临“灾难”</a> 。</p><p>但也有一些积极的故事——比如 Grub Records。运河船上的唱片店Rubber Ducky Records <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/floating-record-store-rubber-ducky-reopens-after-sinking-3564719">去年沉没后也于今年1月重新开业</a>，而经典连锁唱片店<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/classic-uk-music-shop-our-price-to-relaunch-3751144">Our Price也在时隔二十年后于今年重新开业</a>。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/new-music-venue-record-store-grub-records-opens-in-sheffield-3781876">新音乐场所和唱片店 Grub Records 在谢菲尔德开业</a>后首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
